What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Traffic Monitoring Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Traffic Monitoring Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the traffic monitoring market would exhibit a CAGR of 11.16% for the forecast period. Growth in the production of commercial and passenger vehicles especially in the emerging economies, shifting and improving economic conditions of certain economies around the globe and increased focus of the manufacturers on innovative automotive monitoring technologies, surge in the level of traffic and growing proliferation of internet of things technology are the major factors attributable to the growth of traffic monitoring market. This signifies that, the global traffic monitoring market would stand tall by USD 94.03 billion by the year 2028.

From the name itself, it is clear that traffic monitoring refers to a set of solutions, software and services that assist in monitoring and managing the traffic effectively. Not just that, traffic monitoring is a proactive surveillance systems that helps in controlling the traffic infringements, prevent traffic collisions and observe the activities of hazardous drivers. A wide range of tools and techniques are used in the traffic monitoring solutions which are able to record every single information and track the location.

Growth in the demand for the real- time traffic monitoring systems has resulted in growth in the traffic monitoring market value. Growth and expansion of automotive industry especially in the developing economies coupled with rising initiatives by the government persuade the use of traffic monitoring systems will also create lucrative growth opportunities for the traffic monitoring market. Increasing public expenditure to strengthen the safety and surveillance industry will also foster the traffic monitoring market growth. Rising traffic congestion, introduction of MaaS and growing demand for developing smart vehicles compatible with advanced technologies will further carve the way for the growth of traffic monitoring market.

However, high costs associated with the technology and lack of technological expertise in the developing and underdeveloped economies will pose a major challenge to the traffic monitoring market growth rate. Dearth of standardized and uniform technologies will hamper the traffic monitoring market growth rate. Multiple sensors and touch points pose data fusion challenges and this will further restrict the scope of growth for the traffic monitoring market.

